.SH NAME
\*LSgColorChooserSetColor \*O\(em A ColorChooser function that sets the selected color of the ColorChooser
.iX "SgColorChooserSetColor"
.iX "ColorChooser functions" "SgColorChooserSetColor"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Sgm/ColorC.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void SgColorChooserSetColor (\*Vwidget, red, green, blue\*L)
.ta .5i 1.7i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
	short	\*Vred\*L;
	short	\*Vgreen\*L;
	short	\*Vblue\*L;
.wH .fi
.ne 10
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LSgColorChooserSetColor\*O sets the selected color of the given ColorChooser
widget. This means that all the components of the ColorChooser, the color 
hexagon, color sliders, color swatches, and color value text widgets will all
reflect the new color. The given color must be in RGB color space.

.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the ColorChooser widget ID.
.LI "\*Vred\*O"
Specified the red color component in an RGB color space.
.LI "\*Vgreen\*O"
Specified the green color component in an RGB color space.
.LI "\*Vblue\*O"
Specified the blue color component in an RGB color space.
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of ColorChooser widget and its associated 
resources, see
\*LSgColorChooser(3X)\*O.
